Program: Omnibus
Title: Rasputin
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376k2w
Last Broadcast Date: 21 May 1991
'Grigori Rasputin was neither mad nor a monk'. A profile of the self-styled peasant holy man whose influence on Tsar Nicholas II and his wife Alexandra helped bring down the monarchy in Russia. Includes a visit to Rasputin's former apartment and interviews with people who met him.